[[# wanderers-library]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
++ [[span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 125%;"]][[[scp-6000| Nx-01]]]: [http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/ The Wanderers' Library] [[/span]]

[[f>image https://wanderers-library.wdfiles.com/local--files/component%3Atheme/wl_logo.png width="150px"]]

**Area Class:** --##red|**Dunwich**##-- ##666|**Crossroads**##

**Accessible From:** Baseline, Multiverse

**Description:** This vast extradimensional library allegedly catalogs everything that has ever been written down, containing countless books that cannot be found anywhere else, including many documenting the occult and paranormal. Although the Foundation has been aware of the Library since 1955, it has existed for much longer than that. The Library is also known as the Nexus of Worlds and the Great Library Yggdrasil due to its connection to multiple universes, with a particularly close connection to other anomalous libraries such as [[[SCP-1726]]] and [[[SCP-4001]]]. The Nexus and the books within are maintained and protected by various inhuman entities known as [[[wanderers-library-hub|Librarians]]]. Individuals that harm the Library, its books, or its patrons are punished by transformation into one of these Librarians, serving the Library until they work off their debt. This has been the fate of a number of Foundation personnel during incursions into the Library, and so the Foundation has adopted a more diplomatic approach to this specific location. The Library is reportedly headed by an entity known as [[[divine-dossier#the-serpent| The Serpent]]], and serves as the base of operations for GoI-014 ("[[[serpent-s-hand-hub|The Serpent's Hand]]]").

**Associated Articles:**
* [[[*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/wanderers-library-hub|The Wanderer's Library Hub]]]
* [[[yggdrasils-surveyor|Yggdrasil's Surveyor Hub]]]
* [[[Third Law Hub]]]
* [[[another-goddamn-magic-system|Magic Orientation]]]
* [[[Lessons Learned]]]
* [[[secrets-and-their-keepers|Secrets and Their Keepers]]]
* [[[The Black Vaults of Alagadda]]]
* [[[SCP-6000]]] - The Serpent, the Moose, and the Wanderer's Library
* All pages tagged [/system:page-tags/tag/wanderers-library wanderers-library].
[[/div]]

[[# pillar-library]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
++ [[span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 125%;"]]Nx-1726: [[[scp-1726|The Pillar Library]]][[/span]]

**Area Class:** ##666|**Crossroads**##

**Accessible From:** [REDACTED] Province, China, Wanderer Library

**Description:**  The anomalous library of SCP-1726 known as "The Pillar Library" a branch of Nx-01: The Wanderers' Library. SCP-1726 is a library in China containing information philosophical, theological, and historical texts, accompanied by artifacts from civilizations in east and central Asia on ancient anomalous civilisations From the Yeren, Shambhalan dynasties, the Lemurian river peoples, the dynasties of Mu, and the Daevic Empire. The library can only be accessed when accompanied by the animate porcelain statues know as SCP-1726-1 that serve as caretakers.

**Associated Articles:**
* [[[SCP-1726]]] - The Library and the Pillar
[[/div]]

[[# new-atlantis]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
++ [[span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 125%;"]]Nx-5525: [[[new-atlantis|New Atlantis]]] [[/span]]

[[f>image https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/new-atlantis/AtlantisArizonaFlag2.png width="200px"]]

**Area Class:** ##purple|**Free Port**##

**Accessible From:** Glen Canyon Dam, Arizona, USA

**Description:**  The Republic of New Atlantis, also known The Restored Thalassocracy of the Peoples of the Sea, is an Atlantean Colony and a City-State located in Arizona. It was founded by a small number of Atlanteans (//Homo sapiens aquarius//) removed from [[[SCP-5525]]], where they were maintained in stasis within an anomalous device known as the "Untimely Mirror". The Atlanteans were subsequently granted a small region of land around a reservoir by the US Government, which has been developed into a small but secluded city, concealed through techno-thaumaturgy, but heavily monitored by the United States Military. Serving as a continuation of the original Atlantis, New Atlantis has an oligarchic and thalassocratic republic, with the rulers being the Admiralty Board of Senator-Admirals, elected from the New Atlantis Senate. The relationship between Atlantean race and the United States Government is based on the [[[paralaw|Biltmore Treaty]]], which was established with the help of the United Nation's [[[goc-hub-page| Global Occult Coalition]]].

**Associated Articles:**
* [[[Third Law Hub]]]
* [[[new-atlantis|New Atlantis, Arizona]]]
* [[[paralaw|UIU Memorandum — Paralaw Briefing]]]
* [[[SCP-5525]]] - The United States Government Loots Atlantis
[[/div]]

