[[# the-pillars]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]

++ [[span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 125%;"]] FP-05: The Pillars[[/span]]

**Area Class:** ##purple|**Free Port**##

**Description:** An extradimensional space containing a number of gigantic black stone pillars, suspended in an empty void and shrouded constantly by grey fog. Several towns have been constructed on multiple layers within, around and on bridges between these vast structures. Lanterns must remain constantly lit to protect its human inhabitants from hostile entities known as The-Shapes-In-The-Fog.

**Associated Articles:**
* [[[Lantern Bearer]]]
[[/div]]

[[# san-kowloon]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]

++ [[span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 125%;"]] FP-14: San Kowloon (新九龍) [[/span]]

**Area Class:** ##purple|**Free Port**##

**Accessible From:** Hong Kong, China

**Description:** An expansive extradimensional space, formerly part of the Kowloon Walled City in Hong Kong. The Freeport exists due to the lingering effects of [[[SCP-184]]], which was utilized by an unknown party to significantly expand the internal space of buildings within the Walled City. Although these were thought to have been destroyed by the demolition of the city in 1994, it appears that significant portions survived within a pocket dimension. San Kowloon is a labyrinth of interconnected rooms, corridors and stairwells, and is now entirely controlled by Triads, who have divided up San Kowloon between them, creating twelve districts each one controlled by a organization together the "Twelve Lords of San Kowloon". The Foundation and [[[goc-hub-page| Global Occult Coalition]]] are currently working on finding a way into the paranormal enclave, although all attempts so far have failed.

**Associated Articles:**
* [[[SCP-184]]]  - The Architect
* [[[SCP-7250]]] - You Make Your Own
* [[[sammy-skipper-s-fact-of-the-day|]]]
[[/div]]

[!-- Number based on SCP-7035 --]
[[# wonder-world]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
++ [[span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 125%;"]]FP-84: [[[wonder-world| Wonder World!™]]][[/span]]

[[f>image https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/art%3Alocations-of-interest/Wonder-World.svg width="200px"]]

**Area Class:** ##purple|**Free Port**##

**Accessible from:** Boston, Massachusetts, USA

**Surveillance Facility:** [[[secure-facility-dossier-site-55| Site-55]]]

**Description:** Pronounced "Wonder World, Tee Emm," this city-sized extradimensional space serves as the headquarters for the [[[dr-wondertainment-hub|Dr. Wondertainment Corporation]]], which employs the majority of the residents of Wonder World!™ in the research, development and manufacturing of their toys and other products.  In addition to its role as a company town, Wonder World!™ has many of the attractions of a theme park, making it a popular tourist destination for the anomalous community. Permanent inhabitants of Wonder World!™ have been observed to develop changes to their physical appearance, ranging from alterations in pigmentation to more extreme mutations such as the growth of additional limbs.

**Associated Articles:**
* [[[Wonder World Dossier]]]
* [[[city-of-wonder|City of Wonder™]]]
* [[[what-a-wonderful-world|And I Think To Myself...]]]
* [[[vend-a-friend|Vend A Friend (Series Hub)]]]
* [[[SCP-7035]]] - Wonder Coast
* All pages tagged [/system:page-tags/tag/wonderful-world wonderful-world]
[[/div]]

[!-- Free Port number assigned with author's permission --]
[[# parashops]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]

++ [[span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 125%;"]] FP-250: The Parashops[[/span]]

**Area Class:** ##666|**Crossroads**##

**Accessible From:** Baseline, Multiverse

**Description:** Eponymously named, The Parashops are a Free Port marketplace with connections to sites across the anomalous world, [[[wanderers-library-hub| Library]]] included. Within are conventional shops holding wares and everyday products. The place is also home to a massive weekly [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Really_Really_Free_Market Really Really Free Market], where anomalous items change hands freely. The Parashops have no true terrestrial location; the only way out and in is through Ways and other paranatural transportation methods. There are Doors on all seven continents -- but they are ever-shifting mysteries known only for a month at a time.

**Associated Articles:**
* [https://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/lampyra-the-watcher| Lampyra, the Watcher]
* [https://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/take-you-to-the-parashops| I'll Take You to the Parashops]
[[/div]]

